Nexus Engineering S.r.l., in consortium with its partners, is pleased to submit a comprehensive proposal in response to the City of Belval's call for tenders for the implementation of an artificial intelligence solution to assist municipal agents. Our proposed solution leverages our extensive experience in delivering AI solutions, particularly in the public sector, to improve efficiency and quality of service. We aim to provide an intelligent assistance tool that integrates seamlessly with existing practices, enhances access to information, improves response quality, and reduces processing times, all while ensuring strict compliance with regulatory requirements, data sovereignty, and environmental sustainability.

# 2. Understanding of Requirements
We have carefully reviewed the tender documents and understand the City's objectives, including the need for an AI solution that assists agents in their daily missions by facilitating access to information, improving answer quality, and reducing processing times. We are aware of the importance of integrating our solution with existing systems, ensuring high performance and availability, respecting regulatory constraints such as GDPR, and minimizing environmental impact.

# 3. Proposed Solution
### Technical Domain:
Our technical architecture will utilize API gateways for secure integration with existing business software and electronic document management systems. We will leverage containerization tools like Docker and Kubernetes to ensure scalability and high availability, with a targeted p95 response time of under 2 seconds. Monitoring tools such as Prometheus and Grafana will be implemented to track performance.

### Legal Domain:
We guarantee explicit validation by agents for any automated decision-making processes, ensuring transparency and accountability. Our contractual clauses include provisions for data return and destruction upon termination, aligning with GDPR requirements and ensuring data sovereignty.

### Financial Domain:
Our proposed solution is compatible with the City's budget of 3 million euros over 4 years. We can explore cost-optimization strategies, including rate renegotiation with subcontractors or scope adjustments if necessary, to ensure compatibility with the client's budgetary constraints.

### AI and Innovation Domain:
We will design an AI solution leveraging our Large Language Model (LLM) stack, Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) capabilities, and fine-tuning methods. This will provide high relevance of answers and assist agents in drafting administrative contents effectively. Our innovation strategy focuses on knowledge graphs for procedural reasoning and multi-agent collaboration frameworks.

### Sustainability Domain:
To meet environmental sustainability requirements, we will utilize partnerships with green hosting providers like OVHcloud and Scaleway, implement digital sobriety practices such as model quantization and auto-scaling, and aim to achieve ISO14001 certification by 2026. Our carbon reporting capability based on GRI Standards will ensure transparency.

# 4. Compliance & Certifications
We hold an ISO 27001 certification until 2026-11-30, covering the design, development, and operation of AI-powered information systems, ensuring security and compliance. We are experienced with EU regulatory frameworks, including GDPR, and have a Data Protection Officer appointed. Our standard data residency is within the EU, and we utilize anonymization tools to protect sensitive information.

# 5. Budget Overview
Our target gross margin percentage is 28%, with projected revenue of 3 million euros and a projected margin of 840,000 euros for this project. We will work closely with the City to optimize costs while ensuring the quality of service expected, considering strategies such as rate renegotiation or scope adjustments if necessary.

# 6. Conclusion
Nexus Engineering S.r.l., along with its consortium partners, is committed to delivering a comprehensive AI solution that meets the City of Belval's requirements for improving administrative efficiency and service quality. Our proposal integrates technical expertise, legal compliance, financial viability, innovative AI solutions, and environmental sustainability, ensuring a future-proof and effective assistance tool for municipal agents. We look forward to collaborating with the City to bring this vision to life.
