2026-04-29 15:35:09,392 | AGENT | Final proposal generated: **Executive Summary**

Our consortium is pleased to submit this tender proposal for the implementation of an artificial intelligence solution to assist municipal agents in the City of Belval. Our proposed solution leverages cutting-edge AI technologies, including Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) and Large Language Model (LLM) capabilities, to provide intelligent assistance to agents in their daily missions. We are committed to delivering a high-quality solution that meets the City's requirements for efficiency, transparency, and sustainability while ensuring compliance with regulatory requirements.

**Understanding of Requirements**

We have carefully reviewed the tender document and understand the City's objectives, including improving the efficiency of administrative services, enhancing the quality of service rendered to users, and reducing processing times. We acknowledge the importance of respecting regulatory requirements, particularly regarding data protection (GDPR), explicability of AI recommendations, and human validation of automated decisions. Our team is aware of the technical constraints, including performance, availability, integration with existing systems, and sovereignty of data.

**Proposed Solution**

Our proposed solution encompasses several domains:

* **Technical**: We will deploy our AI solution on a SecNumCloud-certified infrastructure, utilizing containerization (Docker, Kubernetes, Helm) and monitoring tools (Prometheus, Grafana, ELK stack) to ensure high availability (99.92%) and performance (p95 response time < 2 seconds). Our API integration expertise will facilitate seamless integration with existing systems, including civil-status and town-planning software, EDM systems, and user directories.
* **AI Innovation**: We will design an AI solution that integrates RAG, LLM, and fine-tuning methods to provide intelligent assistance to municipal agents. Our innovation strategy focuses on knowledge graphs for procedural reasoning and multi-agent collaboration frameworks to enhance the solution's capabilities.
* **Security and Compliance**: We will implement robust security measures to protect data, including hosting within the EU, no cross-border transfers, encryption, and anonymization tools (Microsoft Presidio, custom NER models). Our Data Protection Officer is appointed, and we have experience with GDPR compliance, ensuring adherence to regulatory requirements.
* **Sustainability**: We propose several sustainability measures to reduce the environmental footprint of our solution, including green hosting partners (OVHcloud, Scaleway), digital sobriety practices (INT8/INT4 model quantisation, auto-scaling, query result caching), and responsible electronic waste management through our partnership with Ecologic.
* **Legal**: We will propose contractual clauses that explicitly cover human oversight over AI-driven decision-making processes, transparency in AI recommendations, and compliance with GDPR. Our standard contractual clauses already include provisions for termination, data return, and destruction, supporting data protection principles.

**Compliance & Certifications**

Our consortium is committed to ensuring compliance with regulatory requirements, including:

* GDPR: We have experience with GDPR compliance and have implemented measures to protect data subject rights.
* AI Act: We are aware of the regulatory landscape and will ensure explicability of AI recommendations and human validation of automated decisions.
* SecNumCloud: We will deploy our solution on a SecNumCloud-certified infrastructure.

**Budget Overview**

Our proposed budget for this project is aligned with the City's allocated budget of 3 million euros over 4 years. We target a gross margin of 28%, which translates to a projected margin of 840,000 euros. To optimize costs while maintaining quality, we propose a flexible approach to cost management, including renegotiating rates with subcontractors, streamlining processes, and leveraging technology to reduce expenses.

**Conclusion**

Our consortium is confident that our proposed solution meets the City's requirements for an artificial intelligence solution to assist municipal agents. We are committed to delivering a high-quality solution that ensures efficiency, transparency, and sustainability while respecting regulatory requirements. We look forward to the opportunity to discuss our proposal in further detail and explore how we can support the City of Belval in achieving its digital transformation objectives.
